  "contentHtml": "\n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Mumbai: <a href=\"/tag/fortis+healthcare\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Fortis Healthcare</a> has signed an operations and management (O&amp;M) agreement with real estate firm <a href=\"/tag/dion+group\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Dion Group</a> to expand its foothold to <a href=\"/tag/odisha\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Odisha</a>.The corporate chain hospital said it is set to open a 300-bed <a href=\"/tag/multi-speciality+hospital\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">multi-speciality hospital</a> at Dion Riverside Township, Trishulia in Cuttack.The facility will be located within the Cuttack-Bhubaneswar corridor and will offer tertiary and quaternary care services, advanced diagnostics, critical care infrastructure, and specialised clinical programme, Fortis added.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>This marks Fortis Healthcare's first presence in Odisha and is part of the firm's “broader strategy to expand access to quality healthcare across the country through a combination of brownfield expansion and inorganic growth initiatives, including operating and management agreements and asset-light growth models,” the hospital chain said.</p>\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>“The upcoming 300-bed multi-specialty hospital will play a significant role in improving access to advanced tertiary care services for patients across Cuttack, Bhubaneswar, and neighbouring regions,\" said Dr. Ashutosh Raghuvanshi, Managing Director &amp; CEO, Fortis Healthcar</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>\"This collaboration represents an important milestone in Fortis Healthcare's growth journey and reflects our continued commitment to expanding high-quality healthcare infrastructure across India,\" he added.                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                                                            <!-- <li>By <span>Online Bureau</span>,</li> -->\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <li>By\n                                                                                            <a>Online Bureau</a>\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                        , \n                                                                                    </li>\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/88675629/ETHealthWorld\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ETHealthWorld</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On Jul 6, 2026 at 06:55 AM IST</li> -->\n                                    <li>Published On Jul 6, 2026 at 06:55 AM IST</li>\n                                    <!-- <li class=\"desktop-view\">1 min read</li> -->\n                                </ul>\n                            \n                                        \n\n                    \n\n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n                                            \n                                        <!-- Comment Section -->\n\n                    \n                